article.headline: Georgia Southern edges Georgia State 58-54
article.story: STATESBORO, Ga. -- Mike Hughes scored 15 points, including three 3-pointers, and Georgia Southern shook off a halftime deficit to beat Georgia State 58-54 on Thursday. The teams combined for just 12 points through the first nine minutes of the game. Georgia State closed the half on a 12-6 run -- six from Ryan Harrow -- and led 25-19 at the break. Georgia Southern (16-4, 9-2 Sun Belt) came back in the second half to tie at 41 with 7:36 left on Hughes' 3-pointer. Back-to-back 3-pointers by Hughes and Jake Allsmiller gave the Eagles a five-point lead with 3:47 left. They made 5 of 6 from the line at the end to seal it. Jelani Hewitt had 13 points, nine rebounds, five assists, four steals and a blocked shot off the bench for Georgia Southern. Georgia State (15-8, 8-4 Sun Belt) was led by Harrow's 17 points, while Markus Crider added 14 points and seven boards.
